Don't expect very detail customer service but the staff are nice. You walk to the fridge to get your beverages unless you want horchata water then he will get it for  you. Al Pastor, Carne Asada, and Lengua are just a few of the “meats”, that you can get in your tacos that they offer in this restaurant. Tacos are not the only thing they sell there, they also sell tortas that are very crunchy and delicious. They also sell burritos, that have very juicy meat. They also sell tostadas, platillos, and quesadillas. The quesadillas are very warm and very cheesy. Other than the food the service is also very great. Once you step in you order your food, sit down, and grab your drink. Not even five minutes later your food is at your table warm and ready to be devoured. Their salsa is spicy but not too spicy where you can’t handle it. I usually get tacos, the meat is very warm and very well cooked. Right after you finish eating they immediately clean your table, which allows anyone to sit down right after. It is very clean in there.To pay you go up to the register, now the price is the reason why I gave it ⅘ stars. For 7 tacos and 3 drinks they make you pay $33. That is way over priced, but the food is delicious, so I overlook the price. Overall I really like this place and its food, the service is great and I really recommend it.
